title  · A fun night of code, waffles, and karaoke.

div( class=className )
  section#header: .container: .row.bottom-sm
    .col-xs-12.col-sm-7
      :marked
        <h4 class="highlight">WaffleJS</h4>

        A fun night of code, waffles, and karaoke.
        ==========================================

        ### All proceeds go to [Girls Who Code][1].

        [1]: http://girlswhocode.com/
        
    .col-xs-12.col-sm-5
      :marked
        ##### Date & Time
        ### Wednesday, December 2 at 7 PM

        ##### Location
        ### [SOMA StrEat Food][1] (in the [barn][2])

        [1]: https://goo.gl/maps/0gkOe
        [2]: /map
  
  section#cover-photo

  section#about: .container: .row
    .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
      :marked
        About
        -----

        WaffleJS is a meetup about web technology with a side of waffles
        and karaoke. We meet on the first Wednesday of every month.

        All participants are expected to follow the [JSConf Code of
        Conduct][1].

        [1]: http://jsconf.com/codeofconduct.html
  
  section#get-involved: .container
    h2 Get Involved

    .row.between-xs
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
        :marked
          ### Call for Speakers
          Your talk can be anything from knitting machines to the JavaScript v8 
          engine. And nope, you don't need to be an expert to speak.

        p: a.btn(
          href='https://github.com/wafflejs/wafflejs.github.io/issues/90' )
          | Speaker Details

      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
        :marked
          ### Call for Performers
          You don’t have to be great, just enthusiastic. Try to keep it to 
          around six minutes.

        p: a.btn(
          href='https://github.com/wafflejs/wafflejs.github.io/issues/89' )
          | Performer Details

  section#schedule: .container: .row
    .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
      h2 Schedule

      ul: li( ng-repeat='event in index.schedule' )
        .row.row-lg-offset--3( ng-repeat="(time, item) in event" )
          .col-xs-12.col-lg-3.end-lg
            h5
              | {{time}} 
              span.hide-lg( ng-show='item.type') · {{item.type}}
          .col-xs-12.col-lg-9( ng-show='item.person || item.type' )
            h5.highlight( ng-show='item.person' )
              | {{item.person.name}} · 
              a( ng-href='https://twitter.com/{{item.person.twitter}}' )
                | @{{item.person.twitter}}
          .hide-md-down.col-lg-3.end-lg( ng-show='item.type' )
            h5 {{item.type}}
          .col-xs-12.col-lg-9
            h3( ng-show='item.title' marked='item.title' )
          .col-xs-12.col-lg-9.col-lg-offset-3( marked='item.description' )

  section#sponsors: .container: .row
    .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
      :marked
        Sponsors
        --------

        This month's WaffleJS is sponsored by [Dropbox][1], [Opendoor][2], and
        [New Relic][3].

        [1]: https://www.dropbox.com/jobs
        [2]: https://www.opendoor.com/jobs
        [3]: https://newrelic.com/about/careers

      p: a.btn( href='/sponsorship' ) Sponsorship Details

    .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.row.around-xs.middle-xs
      include ../../images/sponsors/newrelic.svg
      include ../../images/sponsors/opendoor.svg

  section#transparency: .container
    h2 Transparency

    .row
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
        :marked
          ### Finance

          We donate all proceeds every month. Check out [our budget
          spreadsheet][1] to learn more.

          [1]: foo

      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6
        :marked
          ### Planning

          We plan everything out in the open. We track our issues on
          [GitHub][2] and organize on [Slack][3]. Feel free to join and say hi!

          [2]: bar
          [3]: baz
